        public Class<? extends Resource> getResourceClass()
        Returns the class this resource represents. This is used when you need to figure out what the main type of Resource this object is. For example, DefaultFoo, ImplFoo, and SuperFoo may all represent the Resource of Foo, in this case this method may return Foo.class. (Defaults to getClass().)
